<HEADLINE>
MIAOLI COUNTY TO HOLD HAKKA MUSIC FESTIVAL
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taipei, Jan.  15 (CNA) 01/15/07  18:31:38 (By Han Nai-kuo)
</P>
<P>
The Miaoli county government will hold a Hakka Music Festival in
late January and early February to allow Hakka folk song lovers
from around Taiwan to compete in solo and group contests, the
Cabinet-level Council for Hakka Affairs announced Monday.
</P>
<P>
Council officials said the festival is scheduled for Jan. 27-28
and Feb. 3-4, with the preliminary contests taking place at the
county government's Cultural Office Bureau and the finals held in
the county's stadium.
</P>
<P>
The winner of the solo contest will receive NT$100,000, while the
winners in the categories of community groups, elementary and
junior high schools and musical groups will each receive
NT$150,000.
</P>
<P>
The Miaoli county government will accept entries by post only,
with the deadline set for Jan. 19.
</P>
<P>
Information  about the festival  can be viewed  online at
http://honge.honstar.com.tw.
</P>
